        "## 0. 🎯 The Problem: Why You Can't \"Just Ask ChatGPT\"\n",
        "\n",
        "**The Scenario:**\n",
        "\n",
        "Exercise IRON ANCHOR just concluded. You have 25 After-Action Reports totaling 50+ pages. The Regimental Commander needs a lessons-learned brief by 1400. You have 2 hours.\n",
        "\n",
        "**Why Not Use ChatGPT?**\n",
        "\n",
        "You might think: \"I'll upload these AARs to ChatGPT and ask it to summarize them.\"\n",
        "\n",
        "**This violates operational security.**\n",
        "\n",
        "* **Commercial AI services process your data on their servers.** Your exercise AARs contain unit designations, personnel names, operational timelines, equipment capabilities, and tactical procedures.\n",
        "* **Data retention policies vary.** Most commercial LLM APIs retain prompts for 30-90 days. Some use input data to improve their models.\n",
        "* **Adversaries monitor AI training data.** If operational patterns from real exercises leak into training corpora, adversaries can learn U.S. tactics, unit capabilities, and planning processes.\n",
        "* **Even CUI (Controlled Unclassified Information) is prohibited.** Most exercise AARs contain CUI at minimum. Sending CUI to unauthorized systems violates DoD policy.\n",
        "\n",
        "**The Solution: Build Your Own RAG System**\n",
        "\n",
        "Today you will build a Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) pipeline that:\n",
        "\n",
        "1. **Runs on your infrastructure** - No data leaves your control\n",
        "2. **Grounds answers in real documents** - Cites sources for every claim\n",
        "3. **Refuses when evidence is absent** - Won't fabricate information\n",
        "4. **Operates at tactical speed** - Produces briefs in minutes, not hours\n",
        "\n",
        "This is not an academic exercise. This is the operational capability you will need as a staff officer.\n",
        "\n",
        "**Your Task:** Build a system that extracts insights from Exercise IRON ANCHOR AARs while maintaining OPSEC."
      ]
    },
