        "## 5. 🧩 Part 2: Design Decision 1 - Chunking & Embedding\n",
        "\n",
        "This is your first critical design choice. We must \"chunk\" the documents and convert them into vectors.\n",
        "\n",
        "### Task 5.1: Set Chunking Parameters\n",
        "\n",
        "**Chunk Size:** How many words per chunk?\n",
        "* **Too small (50 words):** Loses context. \"BFT outage\" might be separated from \"45 minutes\".\n",
        "* **Too large (500 words):** Adds noise. Model gets entire AAR when it only needs 2 sentences.\n",
        "\n",
        "**Overlap:** How many words overlap between adjacent chunks?\n",
        "* **Too little (0 words):** Information at boundaries is fragmented.\n",
        "* **Too much (100 words):** Redundancy wastes memory and slows retrieval."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": 7,
      "metadata": {
        "id": "0ybwKrtauVBh",
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        },
        "outputId": "9df4c031-1e95-4862-fc32-deab52c60799"
      },
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "stream",
          "name": "stdout",
          "text": [
            "✅ Created 25 chunks from 25 AARs\n",
            "   Avg chunk length: 118.2 words\n"
          ]
        }
      ],
      "source": [
        "# --- YOUR DESIGN DECISION ---\n",
        "# TODO: Choose your chunking parameters\n",
        "# MY_CHUNK_SIZE = 120   # TODO: Set a value (e.g., 80, 120, 200)\n",
        "MY_CHUNK_SIZE = 200   # TODO: Set a value (e.g., 80, 120, 200)\n",
        "MY_OVERLAP    = 30   # TODO: Set a value (e.g., 10, 30, 50)\n",
        "# ----------------------------\n",
        "\n",
        "def chunk_text(txt: str, size:int=MY_CHUNK_SIZE, overlap:int=MY_OVERLAP) -> List[str]:\n",
        "    words = txt.split()\n",
        "    chunks = []\n",
        "    step = size - overlap\n",
        "    for i in range(0, len(words), step):\n",
        "        chunk = \" \".join(words[i:i+size])\n",
        "        if len(chunk.split()) >= 20:  # Minimum chunk size\n",
        "            chunks.append(chunk)\n",
        "    return chunks\n",
        "\n",
        "# Load and chunk all AARs\n",
        "docs = []\n",
        "for p in sorted(base_dir.glob(\"AAR_*.txt\")):\n",
        "    with open(p, 'r') as f:\n",
        "        text = f.read()\n",
        "    chunks = chunk_text(text)\n",
        "    for idx, chunk in enumerate(chunks):\n",
        "        docs.append({\n",
        "            \"doc\": p.name,\n",
        "            \"chunk_id\": idx,\n",
        "            \"text\": chunk\n",
        "        })\n",
        "\n",
        "print(f\"✅ Created {len(docs)} chunks from {len(list(base_dir.glob('AAR_*.txt')))} AARs\")\n",
        "print(f\"   Avg chunk length: {np.mean([len(d['text'].split()) for d in docs]):.1f} words\")"
      ]
    },
