      "source": [
        "### ❓ Question 10.1.1: Justify Your Synthesis Choice\n",
        "\n",
        "**Write your answer here:** [Explain why you chose this K value for synthesis tasks]"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "X_vEGTcVuVBr"
      },
      "source": [
        "**YOUR ANSWER:**\n",
        "\n",
        "I chose a K value of 10 for final synthesis in order to broaden the breadth of information from the provided chunks. Synthesis requires more chunks than a specific Q&A because it has to combine information from multiple sources in order to create a cohesive analysis. Specific Q&A only requires retrieving information about a specific topic at hand and thus requires less chunks. That being said, a high K value will result in more chunks which can introduce false information/noise, causing the robot to hallucinate. As a result, greater retrieval depth (K) will result in lower confidence because the LLM has to process more context into its text embeddings, making it difficult to predict the next word while still incorporating all the provided context.\n",
        "\n",
